---
source: tests/snapshot_tests.rs
expression: stdout
---
ssh-cli: lightweight one-shot binary (spawn‚Üírun‚Üíexit). Multi-host XDG storage without .env. Password
or key auth. No telemetry.

Usage: ssh-cli [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  vps           Manages registered VPS hosts
  connect       Sets the active VPS (writes sibling `active` file in the config directory)
  exec          Runs a command on the VPS over SSH (stdout/stderr captured)
  sudo-exec     Runs a command with `sudo` (safe `sh -c` packing)
  su-exec       Runs a command with one-shot `su -` elevation
  scp           SCP file transfer (upload/download)
  tunnel        SSH tunnel with mandatory deadline (bounded one-shot)
  health-check  Checks SSH connectivity to a VPS
  secrets       Manages the primary key and at-rest secret encryption (one-shot)
  completions   Generates shell completions
  help          Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --lang <LOCALE>
          Forces the CLI language (e.g. `pt-BR`, `en-US`)

  -v, --verbose
          Increases log verbosity on stderr

  -q, --quiet
          Suppresses non-JSON output (quiet mode)

      --config-dir <DIR>
          Configuration directory override (useful for tests)

      --no-color
          Disables colored output

      --output-format <OUTPUT_FORMAT>
          Global output format (text, json). If omitted: JSON when stdout is not a TTY

          Possible values:
          - text: Human-readable text (default)
          - json: Structured JSON

      --disable-sudo
          Disables sudo-exec/su-exec for this invocation (alias --disableSudo)

      --replace-host-key
          Replaces a diverging host key in TOFU known_hosts

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
